    "11 Confusion matrix with actual and predicted classes 1 3 size of the bounding boxes, this measure goes one step further than the Centroid of Rectangles (CoR).",
    "It is possible to think of the IoU as a generalized instance of the CoR.",
    "The (x, y) coordinates of the predicted box of bounding from a detector won't almost certainly match the (x, y) coordinates of the corresponding ground truth bound box in practice.",
    "As a result, this assessment measure rewards overlapping bounding boxes for the ground truth and anticipated boundaries.",
    "IoU ranges from 0 (no overlap) to 1 (perfect overlap) (Breton and Eng 2019)."
